%html
  %head
    %link{:rel => 'stylesheet', :href => '/stylesheets/global.css', :type => 'text/css', :media => 'screen, projection'}
    %script{:type => 'text/javascript', :src => '/javascripts/jquery-1.3.2.min.js'}
    %script{:type => 'text/javascript', :src => '/javascripts/processing.js'}
    %script{:type => 'text/javascript', :src => '/javascripts/freebase.suggest.min.js'}
    = yield :head
    %title Ask Ken - Showcase
  %body
    %canvas#kenviz
    %header
      %section#title
        %h1 ASK KEN™
        %p Visual Knowledge Browser
      %section#search
        %input#fb-suggest{:type => "text", :name => "fb-suggest", :default => "Search 8 million interconnected topics ...", :autocomplete => "off"}
      %br{:style => "clear: both;"}
    %section#content
      = yield
    %aside
      / askken introduction
      %h2 About
      %p
        ASK KEN™ is some sort of a Node-Link diagram that allows to visually navigate through
        interconnected topics provided by the 
        %a{:href => "http://freebase.com"} Freebase
        Service.

        It takes advantage of the latest HTML5 features
        by using the canvas element for drawing.
      %h3 Get started
      %p
        Start using the Browser by just typing in the name of a topic, as you would do in Wikipedia.
      %h3 Quirks
      %p
        Although it’s basically working, the project has rough edges and is far from being complete. There may be some
        unexpected behavior here and there. Also, as the number of nodes increases,
        the performance may drop significantly. So please be aware of that.
      %h3 Credits
      %p
        Thanks to 
        %a{:href => "http://smoofles.at/", :target => "_blank"} Samo Korosec
        for helping with color and layout.
    %footer
      .left
        A
        %a{:href => "http://quasipartikel.at"} Quasipartikel
        Production
      .right
        feeded by
        %a{:href => "http://freebase.com", :target => "_blank"} Freebase
        | Code available at
        %a{:href => "http://github.com/michael/askken", :target => "_blank"} Github
